Subject: Re: [T2] What to use for intake studs

On Monday, August 01, 2005, at 04:10PM, 1970_VW_Westy <1970_VW_Westy(-at-)comcast.net> wrote:

>The two studs on my left intake manifold worked themselves out. Is there 
>a high-temp loctite I can use to prevent this?

Loctite 272 (red) is high temp high strength and rated to 450F but you'll never get the studs out again. Try Loctite 242 (blue) which is rated to 300F.

